"use strict";(globalThis.webpackChunkthe_compendium_of_gronovia=globalThis.webpackChunkthe_compendium_of_gronovia||[]).push([[4610],{6882(e){e.exports=JSON.parse('{"archive":{"blogPosts":[{"id":"/session2","metadata":{"permalink":"/the-compendium-of-gronovia/sessions/session2","source":"@site/sessions/session2.md","title":"Session 2: The Road Ahead","description":"Players: Merla, Cordelia","date":"2026-04-03T15:46:57.463Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"campaign/ruarden-hold","permalink":"/the-compendium-of-gronovia/sessions/tags/campaign-ruarden-hold"}],"readingTime":2.87,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Session 2: The Road Ahead","publish":false,"tags":["campaign/ruarden-hold"]},"unlisted":false,"nextItem":{"title":"Session 1: Ruarden Hold","permalink":"/the-compendium-of-gronovia/sessions/session1"}},"content":"**Players:** Merla, Cordelia\\n## Session Recap\\nLeft in the cold dank warehouse deep in Ruarden Hold, Merla confronted with Duggle heard from him a cryptic rhyme - some kind of warning. Moments later, two dwarves entered the warehouse, forcing Merla and Cordelia into hiding.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\nAs they moved through the halls, they overheard Cecilia ordering a full search of the hold after she discovered what had happened to Trudie, her daughter, and discovering that their rooms were empty. Managing to avoid detection, the players made it to the top of the hold, where Cordelia tripped, alerting a dwarf in the process. Duggle appeared again, this time distracting dwarves, allowing the party to narrowly escape. \\n\\nBeyond the hold, the Balguard mountains, now plump with fresh snow from the previous night\'s blizzard, proved treacherous. The steep terrain paired with the slick ground made the descent dangerous... Cordelia slipped down the mountain side and injured herself, while Merla who was subtly warned by Duggle, managed to navigate the mountain-face with greater ease. \\n\\nEventually the party made it from the mountains into a dense woodland, and eventually to the lakeside village of Cloverstead. There they learned of disappearances in a town far away called \\"Ravenwater,\\" and that Henry Greenwich\'s body had been recovered from there - with the person who found him due to appear before the high court of Venmeer. \\n\\nThat night brought little rest. Duggle appeared again to Merla as she settled into bed, he hinted at lingering magical scars - something haunting her, and offered to listen to whatever burden she carried. In another room, Cordelia experienced a vivid and deeply personal vision in a sleep, Theo appearing to her. Upon waking, she realised another memory had slipped from her grasp, the name of her lover.\\n\\nBoth awoke changed, with a stronger resolve than ever before. Making it to **level 2.**\\n\\nOn the outskirts of Cloverstead, Merla and Cordelia came across a run down house marked with the same insignia found in the basement of Ruarden Hold. Upon their approach they saw wagons outside and the building was heavily guarded by dwarven guards. \\n\\nContinuing along the road, the party came upon a grisly scene. A man laid torn apart near a damaged wagon, and a monstrous, decaying creature feasted upon a horse further down the road. After a dangerous confrontation, the beast fled.\\n\\nHidden within the wagon, they discovered a terrified mother and her young son. The pair had been travelling to Venmeer in search of a new life when they stopped to help what they thought was a stranger in trouble, only to be attacked. \\n\\nWith only one horse capable of pulling the wagon, Merla and Cordelia devised the idea to take the mother and son to Venmeer, having to leave half of their possessions behind while Cordelia took the reigns and Merla walked alongside the wagon. \\n\\nFurther along the road, the party encountered a travelling bard who offered songs for a coin or two. Choosing not to engage, the players ignored the bard incident. \\n\\nWhat felt like many days later, the players had finally reached Venmeer, a sprawling port city and a hub for trade. Towering above the rooflines, the Arlington School of magic loomed, it\'s presence felt across the metropolis. \\n\\nThe mother and child parted ways with the party upon arrival, offering what little they could in thanks. \\n\\nThough the journey had been long, Venmeer had little to offer in the way of respite."},{"id":"/session1","metadata":{"permalink":"/the-compendium-of-gronovia/sessions/session1","source":"@site/sessions/session1.mdx","title":"Session 1: Ruarden Hold","description":"Players: Merla, Cordelia","date":"2026-04-03T15:39:05.170Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"campaign/ruarden-hold","permalink":"/the-compendium-of-gronovia/sessions/tags/campaign-ruarden-hold"}],"readingTime":1.65,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Session 1: Ruarden Hold","tags":["campaign/ruarden-hold"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Session 2: The Road Ahead","permalink":"/the-compendium-of-gronovia/sessions/session2"}},"content":"**Players**: Merla, Cordelia\\n## Session Recap\\nFollowing separate leads tied to forbidden magic, Merla and Cordelia both travelled into the icy Balguard mountains and sought shelter from an encroaching blizzard at **Ruarden Hold**, after being met with at the gate of the hold by a small dwarven child called **\\"Trudie.\\"**\\n\\n{/* truncate */}\\n\\nInside the mess hall, the dwarves grew openly hostile at any mention Ume\xe5, also known as Stubsy. After being offered rooms for the night by Trudie, an encounter with her turned tense after the players attempted to intimidate her, drawing the attention of the dwarven soldiers. They successfully defused the situation, however, before settling in for the night. Later, the players awoke to the sound of a scream and began exploring the stronghold. They uncovered letters that revealed the internal collapse of **The Stonebloods**. Their previous leady, **Henry Greenwich** had been ousted with **Cecilia** taking control, and **Ume\xe5** had become a liability due to his \'carelessness.\' \\n\\nIn the lower cells of the hold, the players found Ume\xe5 who was beaten, starving and barely clinging to life. Bitter and resigned, he directed the pair towards a hidden warehouse beyond a loose stone marked with a distinctive insignia. \\n\\nInside the warehouse, a minor phantom attacked. After defeating it, Merla attempted to free a caged dragonborn, triggering a magical explosion that knocked her unconscious. When she awoke instead of who she thought she freed, Merla instead found a gnome called Duggle Grimsby. Enraged, she tried to attack the gnome that promised to stay with her, insisting that he saw her as a hero. Meanwhile, Cordelia opened a jewellery box containing a ring that spoke to her in her lover\'s voice. Upon wearing it, the ring fused to her finger, stealing the memory of her falling in love with her ex-lover, Theo, and leaving her with the eery feeling she may lose more. A note inside the ring\'s box read: \\"Bento\'s Bazaar, Venmeer\\" - a lead. \\n\\n\\n## Handouts\\n<HandoutGroup session=\\"Session 1: Ruarden Hold\\" />"}]}}')}}]);